#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:22
msgid "Wind Arrows Flow"
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:24
msgid ""
"This example demonstrates how to render fixed-length horizontal wind arrows."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:27
msgid "📋 Summary"
msgstr "📋 まとめ"

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:29
msgid ""
"The sample data contains a longitude and latitude point cloud, along with "
"sample winds provided in the form of three separate eastward (``U``), "
"northward (``V``), and upward (``W``) vector components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:33
msgid ""
"The vector components are measured relative to each spatial sample point in "
"the point cloud."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:36
msgid ""
"No connectivity is provided within the sample data, so each point is a "
"separate location in a field of scattered points, and each point has an "
"associated wind vector independent of the others. We use the "
":meth:`geovista.bridge.Transform.from_points` method, passing the winds with"
" the ``vectors`` keyword, along with the associated sample points to "
"generate a point cloud mesh with attached vectors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:43
msgid ""
"The wind arrows are generated from this point cloud mesh via the "
":meth:`pyvista.DataSetFilters.glyph` method, which creates fixed-length "
"arrows that are coloured relative to the magnitude of their associated wind "
"vector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:47
msgid ""
"Rendering with fixed-length arrows highlights the wind flow and direction, "
"leaving colour alone to indicate magnitude."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:50
msgid ""
"Note that, we only use the horizontal winds (``U`` and ``V``) in this "
"example, which is the most common use case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/generated/gallery/vector_data/wind_arrows_flow.rst:56
msgid ""
":ref:`sphx_glr_generated_gallery_vector_data_wind_arrows.py` for an example "
"of rendering **scaled** horizontal wind arrows."
msgstr ""

